ROLLING HILLS GENERATING, L.L.C. RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 2
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Rolling Hills Generating, L.L.C. (Rolling Hills) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (Reactive Service) from a natural gas-fired peaking generating facility located in Wilkesville, Ohio (Generation Facility) that is interconnected to the transmission system of Ohio Power Company (Ohio Power), an operating company of the American Electric Power Service Corporation (AEP). This Rate Schedule FERC No. 2 sets forth Rolling Hills' revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Power Service from the Generation Facility in the AEP Zone consistent with Schedule 2 of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. Open Access Transmission Tariff.
Rolling Hills' revenue requirement consists of the sum of the charges for the following: (1) The Fixed Capability Revenue Requirement; and (2) Lost Opportunity Costs. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
1) FIXED CAPABILITY COMPONENT
The annual revenue requirement for the Fixed Capability Component is $1,100,000. The monthly charge is $91,666.67.
2) LOST OPPORTUNITY COST COMPONENT
Rolling Hills may receive revenues for Lost Opportunity Costs associated with the Rolling Hills facility. Such revenues must be calculated and distributed in accordance with Schedule 1 of Section 3.2.3(f) of the Amended and Restated Operating Agreement of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C., as amended from time to time.
